results.deck: Domark was a British software publisher founded in the United Kingdom in the 1980s.
results.description: The name Domark originates from the names of its foundedÂ  Dominic Wheatley and Mark Strachan. Domark was active between 1984 and 1995 when it merged with Eidos Technologies, Big Red Games and Simis to form Eidos Interactive, which in turn acquired US Gold and Core Design later. Games published by Domark Software included Badlands, Marble Madness, Prince of Persia, and Syndicate.
